  "title": "Blue's Better Cats",
  "description": "Introduces new cat breeds while updating the existing ones to look more realistic (Optifine/Fabric support)",
  "body": "<center> \n<hr> \n<h3>READ BEFORE USING</h3> \n<hr> \n\nThis resource pack requires Optifine or Fabric + ETF + EMF to work. \n<br> \n\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/F4W91ag.png\" alt=\"Banner - Better Cats version 0.09\" width=\"836\" height=\"255\">\n<hr> \n<h3>HOW IT WORKS</h3> \n\n<hr> The breed of a cat is decided when it spawns. You can get a specific type of cat AND give said cat a custom name using name tags. To achieve this, the name tag must include one of the words on the supported name tags list below. \n<br>\n<br>\n\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/kLNX8G9.png\" alt=\"Breeds and amount of varieties: cats with 1 variation: black, calico, Jellie, Lykoi, Ragdoll, Russian blue, Siamese, Skeleton, Somali, wither skeleton. Cats with 2 variations: Ginger, Persian, Savannah cat, Siberian, Sphynx, Tuxedo. Cats with 4 variations: Tabby\" width=\"836\" height=\"468\">\n\n<hr> \n<h3>SUPPORTED NAME TAGS LIST</h3> \n<hr> \n\n<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/zGjFJFo.png\" alt=\"Supported name tags list in alphabetical order (case-insensitve: Black, calico, ginger (alternative for ginger: red tabby), Jellie, Lykoi, Persian, Ragdoll, Russian blue: (alternatives for Russian blue: russianblue, rb), Savannah cat, Siamese, Siberian, Skeleton, Somali, Sphynx, Tabby, Tuxedo, Wither\" width=\"837\" height=\"576\">\n\n<hr> \n<h3>REANIMATED</h3> \n<hr> \nCats have more realistic animations than before\n\n </center>\n\n",
